# Components / Devre Elemanlar
  res - direnç:      devreyi ve devre elemanlarını yüksek akımdan koruyan devre elemanı. her devrede rastlanır

                     to protect things like LED's and thats because a battery pushes a lot of electrons around a circuit (too much charge!)
                     when we add a resistor, less electrons can flow around the circuit

                    the electrons collide with atoms inside the resistor, and these collisions generate heat. (electron collision vs heat)
                    inside the resistor is a carbon film layer, electrons can flow through this just fine
                    but we cut a helical grove into this, and this creates a narrow path, that makes it very hard for electrons to flow through without colliding  (helical grove cut)

                    flow with resistance    hard      the longer cut, high resistance  for an electron to flow through
                    flow without resistance  easy     the shorter cut, low resistance

                    we calculate the voltage drop require and also, how much energy the resistor needs to remove from the circuit.
                    LED Voltage drop = 2V
                    Current = 20mA  (According to LED Manifacturer)
                    Resistor Voltage Drop:  9V-2V=7V
                    Resistor Value: 7V:0.02A = 350Ω
                    Energy removed (from circuit(P=I^2*R)): (0.02)^2 * 350Ω = 0.14W
                    Min Power rating of resistor: 1/4W (0.25W)

                    and then we select the appropriate size resistor.. otherwise, it can burst into flames
