  diode - diyot:     akımın tek yönlü akmasını sağlar. akımın bir yerden bir yere ya da tam tersi yönde akmasını istemiyorsak diode gerekli
                     ters yönde akan akımları engelleyen devre elemanı.. ters akım devre elemanlarına zarar verir.. 

                      an electronic component that acts as an one way valve.
                      it allows current to flow in one direction but it blocks it in the other direction.
                      we use them to protect our electronic circuits.
                      we can also use it to convert alternating current into direct current. this is called a rectifier.

                      imagine water flowing through a pipe. the pipe has a swing valve installed.
                      as water flows it opens the swing valve.
                      but if the water changes direction, then the swing gate will shut and block the flow of water.
                      thats what the diode is doing to electricity. it only allows current to flow in one direction.
                      but it will break if we exceed its limits..

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
LED - Light Emitting Diode
when we energise it, it produces light.
we get them in many different colors.
inside is a tiny piece of semiconductor material.
the semi conductor is just two special materials joined together. (p-type layer, N-type layer)
and this emits light as photons.
a battery pushes electrons around the circuit. and insidde the semiconductor electrons are jumping from one layer to another.
as they make the jump, they will release a photon particle. 

IF  Visible  UV
   |        |
   700nm    400nm
    red      purple        475nm - blue, 580nm-green

the photon travels in a wave like pattern
different materials produce shorter or longer photon waves.
  GaAsP    Gallium Arsenide Phosphide
  GaAsP:N  Gallium Arsenide Phosphide Nitride
The length of the wave determines the color. the color is not because of the case. 
even this transparent LED, produces a coloured light.
if we apply too much voltage, they will be destroyed.
so we use a resistor to protect the LED.  * * *

